{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id8eae6a4f-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s277"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"277"},"text":"§ 277.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" International Boundary Commission, United States and Mexico; study of boundary waters","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The President is authorized to designate the American Commissioner on the International Boundary Commission, United States and Mexico, or other Federal agency, to cooperate with a representative or representatives of the Government of Mexico in a study regarding the equitable use of the waters of the lower Rio Grande and the lower Colorado and Tia Juana Rivers, for the purpose of obtaining information which may be used as a basis for the negotiation of a treaty with the Government of Mexico relative to the use of the waters of these rivers and to matters closely related thereto. On completion of such study the results shall be reported to the Secretary of State.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id8eae6a50-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1924-05-13/ch153/s1"},"text":"May 13, 1924, ch. 153, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/43/118"},"text":"43 Stat. 118","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1927-03-03/ch381/s1"},"text":"Mar. 3, 1927, ch. 381, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/44/1403"},"text":"44 Stat. 1403","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-19/ch561"},"text":"Aug. 19, 1935, ch. 561","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/660"},"text":"49 Stat. 660","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id8eae6a51-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id8eae6a52-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id8eae6a53-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1935—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1935-08-19"},"text":"Aug. 19, 1935","children":[],"tail":", created the International Boundary Commission to take the place of the three special commissioners."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1927—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1927-03-03"},"text":"Mar. 3, 1927","children":[],"tail":", provided for a study of Tia Juana River in addition to the lower Rio Grande and Colorado Rivers."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id8eae6a54-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"id8eae6a55-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"International Boundary Commission, United States and Mexico, American section, to which powers, duties, and functions of International Water Commission, United States and Mexico, American section, were transferred by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1932-06-30/ch314"},"text":"act June 30, 1932, ch. 314","children":[],"tail":", pt. II, title V, § 510, "